colspan - merges cells horizontally (across columns)



<table border="1">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Name</th>
            <th>Age</th>
            <th>Location</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td colspan="2">Shankar</td>
            <td>NewYork</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Raddhika</td>
            <td>23</td>
            <td>Hyderabad</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>


rowspan - merges cells vertically (across rows)


    <table border="1">
        <thead>
            <tr>
            <th>Name</th>
            <th>Age</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td rowspan="2">Charitha</td>
                <td>23</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
  
                <td>26</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>



EG:-

<table border="1">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Name</th>
            <th>Class</th>
            <th rowspan="3">MVM School</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>Radha</td>
            <td>10</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Ankur</td>
            <td>11</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>




-----------------------------Combination of both-----------------------------


    <table border="1">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th colspan="5">Room Tariff</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td rowspan="3"><b>Room Type</b></td>
                <td colspan="2"><b>Deluxe</b></td>
                <td colspan="2"><b>Executive</b></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><b>AC</b></td>
                <td><b>NONAC</b></td>
                <td><b>AC</b></td>
                <td><b>NONAC</b></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>1500</td>
                <td>1000</td>
                <td>2000</td>
                <td>1500</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>






cellspacing -  It is the gap between the cells


cellpadding - It is the gap we can give inside a cell for content


    <table border="1" cellspacing = "10" cellpadding ="10">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th colspan="5">Room Tariff</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td rowspan="3"><b>Room Type</b></td>
                <td colspan="2"><b>Deluxe</b></td>
                <td colspan="2"><b>Executive</b></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><b>AC</b></td>
                <td><b>NONAC</b></td>
                <td><b>AC</b></td>
                <td><b>NONAC</b></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>1500</td>
                <td>1000</td>
                <td>2000</td>
                <td>1500</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>



--------------Few Other Tags--------------
<small>Display secondary information like copyright Â© 2023</small>
<big>Make text larger for emphasis but use CSS instead</big>
<pre>Preserve formatting like code: function hello() { return "World"; }</pre>
<sub>Create subscripts for formulas: H<sub>2</sub>O</sub>
<sup>Create superscripts for exponents: E = mc<sup>2</sup></sup>
